![A logo with CHAOS, red colored, in the top, and ECLIPSE, greyish colored, in the bottom](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/cached_images/dc0281b9b0be41c7707547ad2d6aa9361a2a89e0.png)


# What is Chaos Eclipse?
My Players' Characters, from my RPG Campaign, are **DEAD** and you must find their Lost Weapons, to know the truth about their Deaths and tell their history for the next generations, while a force from another Dimension, called the **Unknown**, is appearing out of nowhere.

Now what remains is an **Eclipse** that changes everything (TBD) and Creatures from the **Unknown** that are really Chaotic (TBD). 
> Some things should never have left where they came from.

![A line with the Eclipse in the Middle, in Red](https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/cached_images/0c876034e4323ae315ee75d175564640738906fc.png)

This Project is focused on adding tons of New Weapons and Tools, Some Blocks, More End-Game Stuff and Exploration. It's based on my own RPG, which i'm DMing for my friends, all the Features from it are References and Things that exist in the world i created, which are:


## Key Features
- 30 New Weapons/Tools/Magic Items with their own abilities and effects;
  - They can only be found, and have a chance of appearing on chests in structures from the game, making it a journey to find Rare and Powerful Lost Weapons.
- A New Complete Wood Set and a Tree;
  - It grows in the Dark Forest Biome.
- A New Fish and 2 ways it can be prepared;
- 4 "RP Items";
- A New Bean Crop that can be Cooked into an Explosive New Food
- A New Kind of Apple with its own "Variant";
- A New Music Disc;
- A New Ore;
  - That appears in the Overworld and Nether, and you'll need a Netherite Pickaxe to get it.
- A Tool to help find the New Ore;
- A Nice Radio;
- New Types of Drops from Mobs;
  - They're scattered across MANY types of mobs from the game, so going through various places and defeating many types of mobs will be more interesting.
- A New Sniffer Flower;
- A Cute Plushie;
- A Way to Concoct a Strong Random Effect "Potion";
- New Villager/Wanderer Trades;
  - Fisherman, Farmer, Toolsmith, Cartographer, Cleric, **Butcher** and Wandering Trader.
- A Paxel;
- 3 Bizarre Decorative Blocks;
- 11 New Paintings.

<a href="https://modrinth.com/mod/fabric-api" rel="Requires Fabric API"><img src="https://i.imgur.com/Ol1Tcf8.png" width="156"></a> 

[![CurseForge](https://img.shields.io/curseforge/dt/1094831?style=flat&logo=curseforge&label=CurseForge&labelColor=2D2D2D&color=E04E14
)
](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/chaos-eclipse)


### Trigger Warning
This Mod contains some Horror Elements, descriptions of many kinds of Deaths, Mobs may Drop Body Parts like Ears, Eyes, Teeth and Horns and it has a depiction of the Butcher Villager selling and buying those said Parts. It may not be suitable for everyone.



<details>
<summary>FAQ 🔮</summary>

  ## Questions you May ask Yourself
- May i Add this Mod to my Modpack?
  > Of Course! Just remember to give me the credits, and put a link to my Mod Page in the Description or somewhere visible.

- Will you Update/Donwgrade it to X Version?
  > I don't know exactly, modding is kinda new to me, and i'm not very good with coding, if somebody is willing to help, i might! But other than that, probably i'll only update it to future versions, but don't count on it.

- Will you Make a Forge/NeoForge Version?
  > YES! There is a Forge version Now!!

- Does it Work on Quilt?
  > I don't know right now, but a while ago i played with it on a Quilt server and it worked just fine! The code didn't change much, so you probably won't have problems with it.

- Could you Add X Feature/Block?
  > Maybe... i mostly do stuff related to the RPGs and the lore itself, so if you got an idea lore-related, feel free to reach me!

- When you will Add X Missing Feature/Block?
  > I have no idea! Pretty much depends if i have the time, disposition and depending on the difficulty of the task, i maybe won't add it to be honest (i'm looking at you Eclipse, i'll try, but no promises).

- Is this Yout First Mod?
  > Yes!

- What are Your Plans to Future Updates?
  > Right now i'll be focusing in adding some more weapons, from the main RPG and from others me and my friends played, i'll try to add functionallity to the Newspaper, Arcanumrails Tickets and... erm.. the Eclipse, i'm thinking about tools made of **Unknown**'s Essence, Adding some pieces of armor, More Paintings, Some Lore Dungeons/Structures, And if i'm able i'm thinking about some Mobs, a Boss and a Dimension, but keep in mind that all of this is not set in stone and doesn't mean i'll 100% add them.

- Where can i See the Models of the Items with More Detail?
  > Here on my [Sketchfab Page](https://sketchfab.com/juujubs)!

- Is there a CurseForge Page?
  > Of course! Here on [https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/chaos-eclipse](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/chaos-eclipse)!

- I'm having some Problems with X, are there any Known Issues?
  > There are some stuff that no matter how i tried to solve or change them, my short java knowledge wouldn't help me with them, even with tutorials, trying to take a look at other repos, so these are the ones that i know that for now i'll have to keep them this way:
  - The **Eden Tree is kinda Weird**. I tried my best to understand how the trunk placers and foliage placers worked, but i couldn't understand any of it, so the Trees don't look like i really wanted them to look, and they're a little bit weird in shape, this is the best i could do for now, but i'll try to take more looks at it;
  - **Zora's Bow and Pallis' Shield have their Visuals Glitched** if looked by another person in **Multiplayer**? For the person using them, their models will always be correct, since they're done with mixins, because of their changes of states, like visually blocking or pulling the bow and putting an arrow on it, i couldn't get it to work for other people to see it;
  - **Belaios' Wand doesn't Teleport the Player Correctly** sometimes. I tried my best on fixing it, the code of it is like a mess, its like a miracle this is kinda working, most of the time it will teleport you correctly, since it works on the direction you are facing, but sometimes it won't depending on the direction you are looking, a little bit to the ground, for example, and it might consider a place that "doesn't have any empty space to teleport", even tho you are facing a place that has plenty of space to teleport. And for some reason, if you try to teleport from like a really TALL pillar, that isn't supposed to have space to teleport, it will teleport you to the ground in the direction you are facing, for some reason;
  - **The Bean doesn't Spawn** naturally. I don't know exactly how to make it spawn in villages, like a crop would spawn, but you can still buy it from the **Farmer Villager**.


